                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d482">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Loomis</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Clayton</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-07-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 8, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Loomis states that it is reported that three Americans, J. B. Maxwell, J. C.
                    Maxwell, and Enoch Woodworth, were cruelly murdered on the Yaqui River, and
                    instructs Mr. Clayton to invoke the good offices of the Mexican Government for
                    the apprehension and punishment of the murderers.)</p>
            </div>
